  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to collect a saliva sample from patients with a pacemaker to
      study genes involved in cardiomyopathy, a condition where the heart muscle is abnormal.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      DNA will be extracted from the saliva to test for changes in genes related to cardiomyopathy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
